I do feel bad for (possibly) gettin' innocent vendors in trouble, but when it came time for my 20 lashes, I done took 'em Usildor.  Of course I knew it was coming, and it was a bit of a load off my mind.  My only regret, and my apology here is to the vendors that get rolled back...<br>
<br>
Counterfeit laws in real life are the same.  It's the end user of fake money that gets screwed.  If you've ever had a counterfeit bill and brought it to the bank or Secret Service you get a &quot;Thank you,&quot; but you don't get compensated.<br>
<br>
But if a vendor gets rolled back, by definition, it's to a time that they have their merhandise before it was bought.   <p>Hi, my name is Gundark, and I'm an alchemyholic.<br>
